laboratory_examinations.findings: The hepatic echotexture is within normal limits. A 1.1 x 1.1 x 0.8 cm echogenic lesion in segment V of the liver, consistent with a hemangioma. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilation. Common hepatic duct measures 2 mm. The portal vein is patent with normal flow. The pancreas appears within normal limits. The gallbladder is nondistended with no stones. Right kidney measures 10.7 cm. Left kidney measures 11.6 cm. No stones, masses, or hydronephrosis in either kidney. Spleen measures 9.6 cm. Abdominal aorta and IVC are normal in caliber. No ascites. The appendix shows echogenic indurated fat surrounding its tip, directed laterally towards the right iliac wing, with two shadowing appendicoliths in the appendiceal lumen.
